{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"ab850febdcaf47379","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are scanning ~/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/ for the semantic evolution engine and ontology-related code to understand what already exists for the Telos Engine.\n\nRead and analyze these specific files:\n1. ontology.py (~1,348 lines) — What are the 8 ObjectTypes? What's the schema? How are links/actions defined?\n2. decision_ontology.py (~470 lines) — What decision artifacts exist?\n3. temporal_graph.py (~475 lines) — How does temporal concept tracking work?\n4. lineage.py (~462 lines) — How does data provenance work? What Palantir Funnel patterns?\n5. logic_layer.py (~819 lines) — What are the 6 block types? How does deterministic logic work?\n6. guardrails.py (~575 lines) — What are the 5 autonomy levels (0-4)?\n7. message_bus.py (~495 lines) — How does async pub/sub work?\n8. traces.py (~187 lines) — How does the event log work?\n\nAlso look for any semantic_evolution* files (reportedly 4,794 lines across 6 modules):\n- Search for files matching *semantic*, *evolution*, *concept*, *annotation*, *hardening*\n\nFor each file, extract:\n- The TYPE SYSTEM — what types/classes exist\n- The SCHEMA — fields, relationships, constraints\n- The PRINCIPLES — why was it designed this way (from docstrings/comments)\n- The GAPS — what's missing or incomplete\n\nThis is for populating seeds/object-types.yaml and architecture/ontology/ in the Telos Engine.\n\nDO NOT write any code or create any files. This is RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"b2b9683e-efd8-49ec-8093-d2237a092c35","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:47.522Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
