{"parentUuid":"874c9455-c1ad-4aa4-a670-07acd1eda7f9","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"ab850febdcaf47379","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014sc9eap1zw2z4vrgCf4BNt","type":"tool_result","content":"class EdgeType(str, Enum):\nclass HardeningAngle(str, Enum):\nclass ResearchConnectionType(str, Enum):\nclass ConceptNode(BaseModel):\nclass ConceptEdge(BaseModel):\nclass ResearchAnnotation(BaseModel):\nclass AngleVerdict(BaseModel):\nclass HardeningReport(BaseModel):\nclass FileClusterSpec(BaseModel):\nclass ClusterFileSpec(BaseModel):\nclass ConceptGraph:\nclass GravitySnapshot(BaseModel):\nclass SemanticGravity:","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"0c392e36-d73d-47dc-8c8b-1dd18a3fe0c4","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:18.638Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"874c9455-c1ad-4aa4-a670-07acd1eda7f9","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"0c392e36-d73d-47dc-8c8b-1dd18a3fe0c4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab850febdcaf47379","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TfJbJKD7WnpPYoCZTmkSjw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile the comprehensive research report:\n\n## Research Report: dharma_swarm Ontology & Semantic Evolution Engine\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nI've scanned the dharma_swarm codebase comprehensively across 8 core files (ontology.py, decision_ontology.py, temporal_graph.py, lineage.py, logic_layer.py, guardrails.py, message_bus.py, traces.py) plus 7 semantic evolution modules (3,743 lines total). Here's what already exists for populating the Telos Engine's object-types and architecture specifications.\n\n---\n\n## PART I: CORE INFRASTRUCTURE\n\n### 1. **Ontology.py** (1,348 lines)\n**The Foundation: Palantir Foundry Pattern Implemented**\n\n**8 ObjectTypes Defined:**\n```\nPropertyType (enum):     STRING, TEXT, INTEGER, FLOAT, BOOLEAN, DATETIME, ENUM, LIST, DICT, PATH, ID\nLinkCardinality (enum):  1:1, 1:N, N:1, N:N\nSecurityLevel (enum):    PUBLIC, INTERNAL, RESTRICTED, DHARMIC\nShaktiEnergy (enum):     MAHESHWARI, MAHAKALI, MAHALAKSHMI, MAHASARASWATI\n```\n\n**Type System (Schema Layer):**\n- **PropertyDef**: name, property_type, required, default, description, enum_values, ref_type, searchable, immutable\n- **LinkDef**: name, source_type, target_type, cardinality, required, inverse_name, description\n  - Auto-registers bidirectional inverses (1:N becomes N:1)\n- **ActionDef**: name, object_type, description, input_params, modifies, creates, requires_approval, telos_gates, is_deterministic\n- **SecurityPolicy**: read_roles, write_roles, create_roles, delete_roles, classification, field_restrictions, audit_all\n\n**Data Layer:**\n- **ObjectType**: Properties dict, Links list, Actions list, Security policy, telos_alignment (0-1 float), shakti_energy, witness_quality, version, pydantic_model, storage_backend, icon\n- **OntologyObj**: Specific instance with type_name, object_id, properties dict, created_at, created_by, updated_at, updated_by\n- **Link**: Source/target IDs, link_name, metadata\n- **ActionExecution**: Complete audit trail (action_name, object_type, object_id, params, executor, timestamp, result, gate_results, errors, duration_ms)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `register_type()`, `register_link()` (auto-inverse), `register_action()`\n- `get_type()`, `type_names()`, `get_links_for()`, `get_all_links_involving()`\n- `create_object()` — with validation against PropertyDef constraints\n- `execute_action()` — applies telos gates, records to audit log\n- `schema_for_llm()` — context generation for LLMs\n- `serialize()`, `deserialize()` — JSON persistence\n\n**Principles (from docstring):**\n- \"OAG > RAG\" — LLMs receive typed objects, not raw text\n- All mutations through Actions (auditable, reversible, gated)\n- Links are explicit and bidirectional (not implicit FK)\n- Security per-object-type and per-field\n- \"The act of defining IS witnessing\" (v7 rule 5)\n\n**Backward Compatibility:**\n- Maintains Entity/ONTOLOGY API from legacy system\n- Single OntologyRegistry instance (static factory via `create_dharma_registry()`)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No cross-ontology inheritance (parent types)\n- No composite types (object-of-objects)\n- No versioning strategy (version int exists but immutability not enforced)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Decision Ontology** (470 lines)\n**Deterministic decision-quality scoring**\n\n**Type System:**\n```\nDecisionState:       DRAFT, PROPOSED, APPROVED, EXECUTING, OBSERVED, CLOSED\nEvidenceKind:        PRIMARY_SOURCE, REPO_FACT, TEST, BENCHMARK, RUNTIME, USER_CONSTRAINT, MODEL_OUTPUT\nChallengeSeverity:   LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, CRITICAL\nReviewVerdict:       PASS, WARN, FAIL\nDecisionQualityVerdict: FRAGILE, DEFENSIBLE, AUDIT_READY\n```\n\n**Schema (Pydantic models):**\n- **DecisionContext**: mission, owner, time_horizon, domains, constraints, assumptions, risk_score, uncertainty, novelty, urgency, expected_impact, reversible\n- **DecisionOption**: option_id, title, description, selected, tradeoffs\n- **DecisionClaim**: claim_id, text, supports_option_id, evidence_refs, confidence\n- **DecisionEvidence**: evidence_id, kind, summary, source_uri, confidence, verified, provenance_refs\n- **DecisionChallenge**: challenge_id, summary, severity, source_agent, addressed, response\n- **DecisionMetric**: name, baseline, target, measurement_plan, owner\n- **DecisionReview**: reviewer, role, verdict, notes\n- **DecisionRecord**: decision_id, title, statement, state, context, options, claims, evidence, challenges, metrics, reviews, next_actions, kill_criteria, provenance_refs, metadata\n\n**Quality Assessment:**\n- **DecisionQualityAssessment**: overall_score, structural_score, evidence_score, challenge_score, traceability_score, observability_score, verdict, hard_failures, warnings, summary\n\n**Scoring Function:** `evaluate_decision_quality()`\n- **Structural** (22%): title, statement, mission, owner, time_horizon, ≥2 options, selected option, constraints/assumptions\n- **Evidence** (26%): count, diversity (kinds), mean confidence, verified ratio, grounding (PRIMARY/TEST/BENCHMARK/RUNTIME/USER_CONSTRAINT)\n- **Challenge** (18%): steelman check (substantive counterarguments), addressed ratio, severity penalties\n- **Traceability** (18%): claims with evidence, evidence with provenance, option supported, review coverage/quality\n- **Observability** (16%): metric count, completeness, next_actions, kill_criteria\n\n**Hard Failures (Triggers FRAGILE):**\n- fewer_than_two_options\n- no_selected_option\n- no_evidence\n- no_metrics\n- no_counterarguments\n- no_claims\n- selected_option_has_no_supported_claim\n\n**Integration:**\n- `to_decision_input()` — bridges to decision_router.DecisionInput for autonomous/human dispatch\n- complexity_score, domain_count, decision_quality_verdict wired as decision router signals\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Deterministic and artifact-backed\" — structure + grounding + traceability over prose\n- Steelman integration (catches strawman arguments)\n- Reversibility factor (risk_score boost for non-reversible + high impact)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No temporal decision tracking (update history)\n- No dependency graph between decisions\n- No post-action outcome recording\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Temporal Graph** (475 lines)\n**Concept evolution tracking over time**\n\n**Type System:**\n```\nConceptNode:  term, first_seen, last_seen, frequency, sources[]\nConceptEdge:  term_a, term_b, weight, first_co_occurrence, last_co_occurrence\n```\n\n**Schema (SQLite-backed):**\n- **concepts**: term (PK), first_seen (ISO), last_seen (ISO), frequency (int)\n- **concept_sources**: term, source (file path), seen_at (ISO) — UNIQUE(term, source)\n- **co_occurrences**: (term_a, term_b) PK, weight, first_co, last_co\n  - Canonical ordering: a < b lexicographically\n\n**Extraction (Non-deterministic):**\n- Compound terms: `[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*(?:[_-][a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*)+`\n  - Examples: `activation_patching`, `value-space`, `participation_ratio`\n- Single words: `\\b[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*\\b`\n- Filters: min_length=4, excludes 120+ stopwords (English + domain noise)\n\n**Key Queries:**\n- `lineage(concept)` — trace concept through time, sources ordered chronologically\n- `co_occurring(concept)` — find high-weight concept pairs, sorted by frequency\n- `emerging(window_days=7)` — concepts first_seen within window, ≥2 mentions\n- `decaying(window_days=14)` — concepts silent >14 days, historical freq ≥3\n- `hot_pairs(window_days=7)` — strongest co-occurrences in recent window\n\n**Integration:**\n- Used by Garden Daemon archaeology skill for stigmergic marks\n- Feeds into semantic evolution engine for cross-pollination signals\n\n**Principles:**\n- Stigmergy without explicit coordination (marks form via concept frequency)\n- Decay model (silence = signal loss) enables attention rotation\n- Co-occurrence as idea cross-pollination signal\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No concept merging (alias resolution: `activation-patching` vs `activation_patching`)\n- No semantic similarity (bag-of-words only)\n- No strength decay (weight never decreases)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Lineage** (462 lines)\n**Data provenance & impact analysis (Palantir Funnel pattern)**\n\n**Type System:**\n```\nLineageEdge: edge_id, task_id, input_artifacts[], output_artifacts[], agent, pipeline_id, \n             pipeline_label, block_id, operation, timestamp, metadata\nLineageNode: artifact_id, produced_by[], consumed_by[], first_seen, last_seen\nImpactReport: root_artifact, affected_artifacts[], affected_tasks[], depth, total_descendants\nProvenanceChain: artifact_id, chain[], root_sources[], depth\n```\n\n**Schema (SQLite):**\n- **lineage_edges**: edge_id (PK), task_id, agent, pipeline_id, pipeline_label, block_id, operation, timestamp, metadata (JSON)\n- **lineage_inputs**: edge_id, artifact_id (FK)\n- **lineage_outputs**: edge_id, artifact_id (FK)\n- Indexes on: artifact_id (both), edge_id, task_id, pipeline_id\n\n**Key Operations:**\n- `record(LineageEdge)` — atomic insert with inputs/outputs as separate rows\n- `record_transformation(task_id, inputs, outputs, agent, operation, pipeline_id, metadata)`\n- `producers_of(artifact_id)` — immediate parent edges\n- `consumers_of(artifact_id)` — immediate children edges\n- `ancestors(artifact_id, max_depth=50)` — full BFS backward (all input transitive closure)\n- `descendants(artifact_id, max_depth=50)` — full BFS forward (all output transitive closure)\n- `provenance(artifact_id)` — ancestors + root_sources (inputs with no producers)\n- `impact(artifact_id)` — descendants + affected_tasks, depth-tracked\n- `root_causes(artifact_id)` — leaves of ancestor DAG\n\n**Integration:**\n- Called by logic_layer.Pipeline after block completion\n- Metadata can include gate_results, behavioral metrics\n- Supports multi-pipeline tracing (pipeline_id + pipeline_label)\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Every output traces to its inputs\" — no black boxes\n- Thread-safe via per-call connections (SQLite WAL handles locking)\n- Deterministic traversal (no LLM calls in lineage tracking)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No artifact versioning (same ID for all versions)\n- No recomputation detection (can't distinguish changed artifact)\n- No performance metrics (duration of transformation not recorded)\n- No lineage compression (can't prune deep chains)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Logic Layer** (819 lines)\n**Deterministic logic blocks (Palantir AIP Logic)**\n\n**6 Block Types (5 deterministic, 1 non-deterministic):**\n\n| Type | Deterministic | Tokens | Use Case |\n|------|---|---|---|\n| ApplyAction | YES | 0 | Ontology mutation via ActionDef |\n| ExecuteFunction | YES | 0 | Deterministic callable (sync/async) |\n| Conditional | YES | 0 | if/else branching on context state |\n| Loop | YES | 0 | Iterate over items with body block |\n| CreateVariable | YES | 0 | Set a value in context.state |\n| UseLLM | NO | ~max_tokens | Non-deterministic LLM call |\n\n**Schema:**\n- **BlockKind**: enum (6 variants)\n- **BlockStatus**: PENDING, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILED, SKIPPED, BLOCKED\n- **BlockResult**: block_id, kind, status, output, error, duration_seconds, deterministic (bool), tokens_used, started_at, finished_at, child_results\n- **ExecutionContext**: state (dict), registry, gate_fn, llm_fn, metadata\n  - Methods: `get(key)`, `set(key, value)`, `resolve(template)`, `resolve_dict(params)`\n- **Pipeline**: blocks[], label, pipeline_id, stop_on_failure (bool)\n- **PipelineResult**: pipeline_id, label, status, block_results, total_duration_seconds, total_tokens, deterministic_blocks, nondeterministic_blocks, deterministic_ratio, started_at, finished_at\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `ApplyAction.execute()` — calls registry.execute_action() with resolved params, runs gate_fn if present\n- `Conditional.execute()` — evaluates predicate, runs if_true or if_false child\n- `Loop.execute()` — calls items_fn(context), iterates up to max_iterations, sets context[item_var]\n- `UseLLM.execute()` — marks deterministic=False, calls context.llm_fn(prompt, config), tracks tokens\n- `Pipeline.execute()` — runs blocks sequentially, accumulates metrics, calls on_block_complete hook\n\n**PipelineBuilder Fluent API:**\n```python\n.set(name, value)\n.call(func, args={}, store_as=\"\")\n.action(object_type, action_name, params={}, store_as=\"\")\n.branch(condition, if_true, if_false, store_as=\"\")\n.loop(items_fn, body, item_var=\"item\", max_iterations=100, store_as=\"\")\n.llm(prompt_template, store_as=\"llm_output\", max_tokens=1024, model=\"\")\n.add(block)\n.build() → Pipeline\n```\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"80% deterministic, 20% LLM\" goal (from Palantir at nation-state scale)\n- Blocks can't modify execution flow (no break/continue/goto)\n- Token budget tracked but not enforced\n- Template variable resolution: `{variable_name}` replaced from context.state\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No parallel block execution (async but sequential within pipeline)\n- No error recovery (only stop_on_failure or skip)\n- No block timeout enforcement\n- No resource quota per block\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Guardrails** (575 lines)\n**Parallel validation layer (5 autonomy levels)**\n\n**Autonomy Levels (Anduril-style):**\n```\n0 = HUMAN_ONLY          — Human must perform action\n1 = HUMAN_SUPERVISED    — AI suggests, human approves\n2 = HUMAN_ON_LOOP       — AI acts, human monitors & can veto\n3 = AUTONOMOUS_ALERT    — AI acts, alerts human after\n4 = FULLY_AUTONOMOUS    — AI acts without human involvement\n```\n\n**3 Guardrail Types:**\n- **InputGuardrail**: Validates before/during execution (BLOCKING or PARALLEL mode)\n- **OutputGuardrail**: Validates result before accepting (always BLOCKING, sequential)\n- **ToolGuardrail**: Intercepts individual tool/action calls\n\n**Verdict Hierarchy:**\n```\nGuardrailVerdict: PASS, WARN, FAIL, TRIPWIRE (immediate halt, no recovery)\n```\n\n**Schema:**\n- **GuardrailContext**: action, content, tool_name, agent, task_id, autonomy_level, metadata\n- **GuardrailResult**: guardrail_id, guardrail_name, verdict, reason, mode, duration_seconds, details, timestamp\n- **GuardrailSummary**: passed (bool), tripwire (TripwireResult), results[], total_duration_seconds, blocking_count, parallel_count, pass/warn/fail counts\n\n**Built-in Guardrails:**\n- **TelosInputGuardrail**: Wraps existing 11-gate system (TelosGatekeeper)\n  - Tier A/B failures → FAIL, Tier C → WARN, all pass → PASS\n- **AutonomyGuardrail**: Enforces autonomy_level constraints\n  - Higher-risk actions require lower autonomy (more human oversight)\n- **ContentLengthGuardrail**: Validates output within min/max char bounds\n- **MimicryGuardrail**: Detects performative outputs via MetricsAnalyzer\n- **ActionTypeGuardrail**: Checks action exists & warns on dangerous tools (bash, shell, exec, eval, subprocess)\n- **CallableGuardrail**: Custom one-off check from arbitrary function\n\n**GuardrailRunner Orchestration:**\n- Sequential blocking guardrails first (stop on TRIPWIRE or FAIL)\n- Parallel guardrails run concurrently if blocking all pass\n- Output guardrails always sequential\n- Tool guardrails sequential before each tool call\n\n**Integration:**\n- logic_layer.Pipeline can wire guardrails to ExecutionContext\n- ontology.ActionDef.telos_gates → ToolGuardrails\n- decision_router routes to autonomy level → AutonomyGuardrail enforcement\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Validation alongside execution\" (OpenAI Agents SDK pattern)\n- Blocking vs parallel tradeoff (latency vs coverage)\n- Tripwire for existential threats (no recovery)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No guardrail priority ordering\n- No guardrail timeouts\n- No shared state between guardrails\n- No guardrail result caching (re-run same check twice)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Message Bus** (495 lines)\n**Async SQLite pub/sub for inter-agent communication**\n\n**Type System:**\n```\nMessage:       id, from_agent, to_agent, subject, body, priority, status, \n               created_at, read_at, reply_to, metadata\nMessagePriority: URGENT, HIGH, NORMAL, LOW\nMessageStatus:  UNREAD, READ\nArtifact:      id, message_id, artifact_type, content, summary, files_touched[], \n               metadata, created_at\n```\n\n**Schema (aiosqlite, async):**\n- **messages**: id (PK), from_agent, to_agent, subject, body, priority, status, created_at, read_at, reply_to, metadata (JSON)\n- **heartbeats**: agent_id (PK), last_seen, status, metadata (JSON)\n- **subscriptions**: (agent_id, topic) PK, created_at\n- **artifacts**: id (PK), message_id (FK), artifact_type, content, summary, files_touched (JSON), metadata (JSON), created_at\n- Indexes on: to_agent, status, priority, topic, message_id\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `send(message)` → message_id\n- `receive(agent_id, status=\"unread\", limit=50)` — priority-ordered (URGENT→HIGH→NORMAL→LOW), then by created_at DESC\n- `mark_read(msg_id)` — set status='read', read_at=now\n- `reply(original_id, from_agent, body)` → new message_id\n- `subscribe(agent_id, topic)`, `publish(topic, message)` — fan-out to all subscribers\n- `heartbeat(agent_id, metadata={})` — upsert\n- `get_agent_status(agent_id)` → {last_seen, status, age_minutes, metadata} or None\n- `get_stats()` → {total_messages, unread_messages, unread_by_agent, known_agents}\n- `attach_artifact(message_id, artifact_type, content, summary, files_touched, metadata)` → artifact_id\n- `get_artifacts(message_id, artifact_type=None)` → list of dicts\n- `send_with_artifacts(message, artifacts=[])` — atomic transaction\n- `build_context_from_artifacts(agent_id, budget=5000)` — format unread + artifacts into context string\n\n**Integration:**\n- All methods async (non-blocking I/O via aiosqlite)\n- Artifact types from mission_contract.ArtifactType (code_diff, analysis, etc.)\n- Used by trishula/mycelium for cross-system agent comms\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"No global singletons\" — per-instance connections\n- Priority dispatch (urgent first, regardless of order)\n- Heartbeat as liveness signal (10-minute timeout = offline)\n- Artifacts as first-class (typed, searchable, linked to messages)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No message encryption/signing\n- No delivery guarantees (fire-and-forget)\n- No message TTL/expiration\n- No message search/query beyond agent_id\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Traces** (187 lines)\n**Event log for swarm action tracking**\n\n**Type System:**\n```\nTraceEntry: id, timestamp, agent, action, state, parent_id, fitness, \n            files_changed[], metadata\n```\n\n**Schema (JSON-backed, atomic writes):**\n- **history/**: `{id}.json` files, one per event\n- **archive/**: old entries moved here (>24 hours by default)\n- **patterns/**: derived patterns (unused in current code)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `log_entry(entry)` — atomic JSON write to history/{entry.id}.json via tempfile+os.replace()\n- `get_entry(entry_id)` — load from history/{id}.json\n- `get_recent(limit=20)` — all history files, sorted by timestamp DESC\n- `get_lineage(entry_id)` — walk parent_id chain back to root\n- `archive_old(max_age_hours=24)` — move old entries to archive/ directory\n\n**Integration:**\n- Called by agent_runner after task completion\n- parent_id enables event trees (task_spawned → subtask → task_completed)\n- fitness (FitnessScore) tracks evolution metrics\n\n**Principles:**\n- Atomic writes (tempfile + rename) avoid partial writes on crash\n- Async via asyncio.to_thread (non-blocking)\n- Human-readable JSON (not binary)\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No trace compression\n- No indexing (all N files scanned on get_recent)\n- No trace analysis/aggregation\n- No timestamp range queries\n\n---\n\n## PART II: SEMANTIC EVOLUTION ENGINE (3,743 lines across 7 modules)\n\n### Architecture Overview\n**Phase-based semantic enrichment:**\n1. **DIGEST** (semantic_digester.py, 880 lines): Extract concepts from source files\n2. **RESEARCH** (semantic_researcher.py, 420 lines): Annotate with external knowledge\n3. **SYNTHESIZE** (semantic_synthesizer.py, 358 lines): Generate file clusters from intersections\n4. **HARDEN** (semantic_hardener.py, 677 lines): Multi-angle quality verification\n5. **GRAVITY** (semantic_gravity.py, 658 lines): Concept graph & lattice tightening\n6. **BRIDGE** (semantic_memory_bridge.py, 430 lines): Wire into agent memory system\n7. **COMPILE** (semantic_briefs.py, 320 lines): Promote clusters to decision briefs\n\n### 9. **Semantic Digester** (880 lines)\n**Phase 1: Deep source file reading**\n\n**Extraction Strategy:**\n- **Python files**: AST-parsed docstrings, class/function names, import graph, formal pattern detection\n- **Markdown files**: Header hierarchy, bold-defined terms, claim sentences, YAML/code-fenced blocks\n- **Both**: Behavioral profiling via MetricsAnalyzer, connection finding via ouroboros\n\n**Formal Patterns Detected (22 regex patterns):**\n```\nmonad, coalgebra, sheaf, cohomology, functor, distributive_law, fixed_point,\nmanifold, geodesic, fisher_metric, participation_ratio, kleisli, idempotent,\nbisimulation, stigmergy, anekanta, dharmic, ouroboros, entropy, kolmogorov_complexity, R_V\n```\n\n**Claim Indicators (regex):**\n```\nmust, shall, always, never, invariant, guarantee, ensure, require,\nimplies, therefore, thus, hence, consequently,\nhypothesis, conjecture, claim, assert, proof, theorem, lemma,\nthreshold, constraint, bound, limit, floor, ceiling\n```\n\n**Category Classification:**\n- Mathematical, Philosophical, Engineering, Measurement\n\n**Output:**\n- ConceptNode for each extracted concept\n- ConceptEdge for import/reference relationships\n- ConceptGraph populated with concepts + edges\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `digest_file(path, graph)` — read single file, extract concepts\n- `digest_directory(path, graph)` — recursive scan, skip common dirs (.git, __pycache__, .venv)\n- `_extract_python_concepts()` — AST parsing\n- `_extract_md_concepts()` — regex + header parsing\n\n**Integration:**\n- Called by semantic evolution daemon weekly\n- Output feeds RESEARCH phase\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"All failures are non-fatal\" — skip unreadable files, log warnings\n- Pattern-based extraction (no ML/LLM at ingest)\n- Behavioral profiling via existing MetricsAnalyzer\n\n**Gaps Observed:**\n- No semantic deduplication (same concept extracted multiple times)\n- No conflicting claim detection\n- No comment-to-code linkage\n- No function signature parsing for type hints\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Semantic Gravity** (658 lines)\n**The Core Data Structures**\n\n**ConceptNode:**\n```\nid, name, definition, source_file, source_line, category,\nclaims[], formal_structures[], salience (0-1), semantic_density,\nbehavioral_entropy, behavioral_complexity, recognition_type, metadata,\ncreated_at\n```\n\n**ConceptEdge:**\n```\nid, source_id, target_id, edge_type (EdgeType enum), weight, \ndefinition, confidence, created_at\n```\n\n**EdgeType (8 variants):**\n```\nDEPENDS_ON, IMPLEMENTS, EXTENDS, CONTRADICTS, ANALOGOUS_TO, IMPORTS, REFERENCES, GROUNDS\n```\n\n**ResearchAnnotation:**\n```\nid, concept_id, citation, external_source, connection_type (ResearchConnectionType),\nconfidence, field, summary, created_at\n```\n\n**ResearchConnectionType (4 variants):**\n```\nVALIDATION, CONTRADICTION, ORTHOGONAL, ENGINEERING_GROUNDING\n```\n\n**FileClusterSpec:**\n```\nid, name, description, files[], core_concepts[], research_annotations[],\nhardening_score, gravitational_mass, created_at\n```\n\n**ClusterFileSpec:**\n```\npath, role (core|test|grounding|satellite), imports_from[], exports_to[], size_bytes\n```\n\n**HardeningReport:**\n```\ncluster_id, overall_score, passed (bool), angles (dict[HardeningAngle→AngleVerdict]),\nfailed_angles[], suggested_refinements[], timestamp\n```\n\n**HardeningAngle (6 variants):**\n```\nMATHEMATICAL, COMPUTATIONAL, ENGINEERING, CONTEXT_ENGINEERING, SWARM_DYNAMICS, BEHAVIORAL_HEALTH\n```\n\n**AngleVerdict:**\n```\nangle (HardeningAngle), result (GateResult: PASS/WARN/FAIL), score, gaps[]\n```\n\n**ConceptGraph:**\n- `all_nodes()`, `get_node(id)` → ConceptNode\n- `all_edges()`, `edges_from(source_id)`, `edges_to(target_id)` → ConceptEdge[]\n- `degree(node_id)` → int (in-degree + out-degree)\n- `high_salience_nodes(threshold=0.4)` → ConceptNode[]\n- `get_annotation(id)` → ResearchAnnotation\n- `get_cluster(id)` → FileClusterSpec\n- `ancestors(node_id, max_depth=50)` → ConceptNode[] (BFS backward)\n- `descendants(node_id, max_depth=50)` → ConceptNode[] (BFS forward)\n\n**SemanticGravity:**\n- `compute_mass(cluster)` → concept_count × cross_reference_count × hardening_score\n- `tighten_lattice()` → strengthen dense clusters, decay weak ones\n- `snapshot()` → GravitySnapshot (time-series tracking)\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Gravitational metaphor\": density attracts related ideas\n- Salience as central signal (emergence threshold ~0.4)\n- Hardening score as quality multiplier\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Semantic Researcher** (420 lines)\n**Phase 2: External knowledge annotation**\n\n**Research Knowledge Base (hardcoded 2026 connections):**\n- **monad**: Moggi (1991), Haskell IO Monad, validation/engineering_grounding\n- **coalgebra**: Rutten (2000), Sangiorgi bisimulation (2011), validation/concurrency\n- **sheaf**: Curry (2014), Robinson sheaf neural networks (2022), validation/orthogonal\n- **cohomology**: Ghrist (2014), sensor networks, validation/topology\n- **stigmergy**: Parunak (2026) AAMAS, swarm agents, validation\n- Plus 30+ additional domain mappings\n\n**Three-Altitude Strategy:**\n- **Summit**: Meta-concept, field membership\n- **Stratosphere**: 2026 research/production systems\n- **Ground**: Specific papers, frameworks, systems\n\n**Output:**\n- ResearchAnnotation for each high-salience concept\n- Citation records for grounding\n- Connection types (validation, contradiction, orthogonal, engineering_grounding)\n\n**Integration:**\n- Runs after DIGEST\n- Feeds into SYNTHESIZE (research_annotations inform cluster generation)\n- No live web search (offline compiled knowledge)\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Compiled knowledge\" enables fast annotation without LLM calls\n- Confidence scores distinguish strong vs weak connections\n- Three-layer signal prevents false positives\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Semantic Synthesizer** (358 lines)\n**Phase 3: Engineering cluster generation**\n\n**ConceptIntersection:**\n```\nconcepts[], shared_structures[], shared_annotations[], score\nname property → \" × \".join(concept names)\n```\n\n**Cluster Synthesis Rules:**\n1. Two concepts sharing formal structure → potential cluster\n2. Two concepts sharing research annotations in same field → potential cluster\n3. Two connected concepts (edge) with high salience → potential cluster\n\n**FileClusterSpec Generation:**\n- 3-7 files per cluster\n- 1 core concept file (.py with running code)\n- 1 grounding spec (.md with formal claims)\n- 1 test file\n- 0-4 satellite files (supporting modules)\n\n**Output:**\n- FileClusterSpec with file paths, roles, dependencies\n- Ready for code generation or Darwin Engine materialization\n\n**Integration:**\n- Consumes RESEARCH phase output (ConceptGraph + ResearchAnnotations)\n- Feeds into HARDEN phase\n\n**Principles:**\n- Intersections → actionable clusters\n- Minimum 3 files (too small = noise)\n- Maximum 7 files (too large = lacks cohesion)\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Semantic Hardener** (677 lines)\n**Phase 4: Multi-angle quality verification**\n\n**Six Hardening Angles:**\n\n| Angle | Checks | Score Function |\n|-------|--------|---|\n| **Mathematical** | Formal structures present, referenced, definitions non-empty, concept degree >0 | 0.7→PASS, 0.4→WARN, <0.4→FAIL |\n| **Computational** | Files importable, no syntax errors, test stubs present | Importability × syntax_ok × test_coverage |\n| **Engineering** | MetricsAnalyzer behaviors: entropy, complexity, compression ratio | behavioral signatures |\n| **Context Engineering** | Docstring density, cross-reference completeness | Mean docs/function, links satisfied |\n| **Swarm Dynamics** | Sheaf-style cohomological connectivity (cluster coherence) | Degree/density ratios |\n| **Behavioral Health** | Ouroboros behavioral scoring, mimicry detection | Entropy + complexity + no_mimicry |\n\n**HardeningReport:**\n- overall_score = weighted average of 6 angles\n- passed (bool) = all angles ≥0.7 OR no FAIL verdicts\n- failed_angles[] → feedback for next iteration\n- suggested_refinements[] → actionable improvement steps\n\n**Integration:**\n- Consumes FileClusterSpec from SYNTHESIZE\n- Rejects weak clusters (score <0.6)\n- Generates gaps for DIGEST feedback loop\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Orthogonal angles\" — each checks different dimension\n- Non-fatal failures → refinement suggestions instead of rejection\n- Multi-iteration convergence (gaps → next DIGEST cycle)\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Semantic Memory Bridge** (430 lines)\n**Phase 5: Wiring into agent memory**\n\n**Five Bridge Functions:**\n\n1. **Concepts → UnifiedIndex**\n   - Index every ConceptNode for hybrid retrieval (lexical + overlap + semantic)\n   - Metadata: source_kind=semantic_concept, concept_id, salience, formal_structures, recognition_type\n\n2. **Retrieval Uptake → Salience**\n   - Agent retrieval increments concept salience\n   - Feedback loop: used concepts become more prominent\n\n3. **Idea Shards → Research**\n   - Conversation insights (idea_shards) become research candidates\n   - Stored as ConceptNode + ResearchAnnotation\n\n4. **Sleep Semantic Phase**\n   - During sleep consolidation, run one semantic evolution cycle\n   - Integrate new concepts from conversation history\n\n5. **Experiment Memory → Hardening**\n   - Failure patterns inform hardening gaps\n   - Failure clusters → refinement suggestions\n\n**Integration:**\n- Wires semantic_digester output into UnifiedIndex\n- Called by memory consolidation daemon\n- Feedback from agent queries → salience updates\n\n**Principles:**\n- \"Living ontology\" — concepts evolve with agent use\n- Bidirectional flow: concepts inform agents, agent usage refines concepts\n- Sleep cycles compress semantic space\n\n---\n\n### 15. **Semantic Briefs Compiler** (320 lines)\n**Phase 6: Decision-grade compilation**\n\n**SemanticBrief (Mission Contract):**\n```\nid, name, summary, evidence[], citations[],\nreadiness_score, suggested_actions[]\n```\n\n**Compilation Rules:**\n- Rank clusters by: hardening_report.passed DESC, overall_score DESC, gravitational_mass DESC\n- Take top N (default 3)\n- Extract concept names, citations, evidence files\n- Calculate readiness = (cluster.hardening_score × 0.35) + (report.overall_score × 0.65) + (passed ? +0.05 : 0)\n\n**Output:**\n- Campaign-grade briefs ready for human/AI decision-making\n- Linked to ontology actions\n\n**Integration:**\n- Final output of semantic evolution pipeline\n- Feeds into decision_router via ontology\n\n**Principles:**\n- Promotion criteria (hardening + cluster mass)\n- Readiness metric guides prioritization\n- Traceability to source files + citations\n\n---\n\n## PART III: INTEGRATION PATTERNS\n\n### Complete Flow: Ontology → Decision → Execution\n\n```\n1. OntologyRegistry.create_dharma_registry()\n   ↓\n2. Register ObjectTypes (Agent, Experiment, Research Thread, etc.)\n   ↓\n3. Semantic digester finds concepts in source code\n   ↓\n4. Semantic researcher annotates with external knowledge\n   ↓\n5. Semantic synthesizer generates FileClusterSpec\n   ↓\n6. Semantic hardener validates clusters (6 angles)\n   ↓\n7. Semantic memory bridge indexes concepts into UnifiedIndex\n   ↓\n8. Decision ontology captures decision record\n   ↓\n9. Decision quality assessment (structural/evidence/challenge/traceability/observability)\n   ↓\n10. Logic layer pipeline: ApplyAction → ontology.execute_action()\n    ↓\n11. Guardrails: InputGuardrail (telos_gates) → execution\n    ↓\n12. ActionExecution records audit trail\n    ↓\n13. Lineage tracks: inputs → outputs → downstream impact\n    ↓\n14. Traces stores event log with parent_id chains\n    ↓\n15. Temporal graph tracks concept evolution over time\n```\n\n---\n\n## PART IV: GAPS & OPPORTUNITIES FOR TELOS ENGINE\n\n### Type System Gaps\n- [ ] No inheritance/composition for ObjectTypes\n- [ ] No versioning enforcement (version int exists but immutability not enforced)\n- [ ] No property constraints beyond type (no min/max, regex patterns, custom validators)\n- [ ] No enum validation beyond static lists\n- [ ] No temporal properties (validity window, snapshot dates)\n\n### Semantic Evolution Gaps\n- [ ] No concept merging/aliasing (activation-patching vs activation_patching)\n- [ ] No conflicting claim detection\n- [ ] No circular dependency detection in concept graph\n- [ ] No concept lifecycle (creation → maturation → archival)\n- [ ] No concept versioning (track definition evolution)\n\n### Decision & Governance Gaps\n- [ ] No decision reuse/template system\n- [ ] No multi-stage approval workflow\n- [ ] No post-decision outcome recording\n- [ ] No decision dependencies (can't say \"this blocks that decision\")\n- [ ] No rollback mechanism (decisions can't be undone)\n\n### Lineage & Traceability Gaps\n- [ ] No artifact versioning (same ID for all versions)\n- [ ] No performance metrics (transformation duration)\n- [ ] No lineage compression (can't prune deep chains)\n- [ ] No circular dependency detection\n- [ ] No cost/resource attribution\n\n### Execution & Safety Gaps\n- [ ] No block-level timeout enforcement\n- [ ] No resource quota per block (memory, CPU, tokens)\n- [ ] No parallel block execution (async but sequential)\n- [ ] No error recovery policies (only stop_on_failure or skip)\n- [ ] No guardrail result caching (re-run same check twice)\n- [ ] No autonomy-aware fallback routing\n\n### Memory & Retrieval Gaps\n- [ ] No concept lifecycle search (show concepts → active → stale → retired)\n- [ ] No co-citation analysis (papers citing same concepts)\n- [ ] No concept similarity/clustering (beyond exact term match)\n- [ ] No temporal concept search (concepts at time T)\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Module | Lines | Type System | Key Concept | State |\n|--------|-------|---|---|---|\n| ontology.py | 1348 | PropertyDef, LinkDef, ActionDef, ObjectType, Link | Palantir Foundry pattern for dharma_swarm | **COMPLETE** |\n| decision_ontology.py | 470 | DecisionRecord, DecisionQualityAssessment | Deterministic decision scoring | **COMPLETE** |\n| temporal_graph.py | 475 | ConceptNode, ConceptEdge | Concept evolution over time | **COMPLETE** |\n| lineage.py | 462 | LineageEdge, ProvenanceChain, ImpactReport | Data provenance (Funnel pattern) | **COMPLETE** |\n| logic_layer.py | 819 | LogicBlock (6 types), ExecutionContext, Pipeline | Deterministic logic blocks (AIP pattern) | **COMPLETE** |\n| guardrails.py | 575 | Guardrail (3 types), AutonomyLevel (5 levels) | Parallel validation layer | **COMPLETE** |\n| message_bus.py | 495 | Message, Artifact (typed) | Async inter-agent pub/sub | **COMPLETE** |\n| traces.py | 187 | TraceEntry | Event log with lineage | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_digester.py** | **880** | ConceptNode, ConceptEdge | Extract from source files (22 patterns) | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_gravity.py** | **658** | ConceptGraph, FileClusterSpec, HardeningReport | Concept lattice + file clusters | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_researcher.py** | **420** | ResearchAnnotation (30+ fields mapped) | Annotate with 2026 knowledge | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_synthesizer.py** | **358** | ConceptIntersection, FileClusterSpec | Generate 3-7 file clusters | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_hardener.py** | **677** | HardeningReport (6 angles) | Multi-angle quality verification | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_memory_bridge.py** | **430** | 5 bridge functions | Wire semantic→memory system | **COMPLETE** |\n| **semantic_briefs.py** | **320** | SemanticBrief, readiness_score | Decision-grade compilation | **COMPLETE** |\n\n---\n\n## Key File Locations (Absolute Paths)\n\nCore Infrastructure:\n- `/User